arch:property.oc:show_val: L34 is hard clayey fill below the level of the surface in L29. After cleaning off L29 we leveled the rest of L22 to the bottom of L29. The entire area was the same type of soil so we changed the whole locus to L34. We extended the fill adjacent to pedastalled mudbrick wall L39 and L38 because these areas were also the same fill. We thought there may be more mudbrick adjacent to L37 surface so we isolated the are of different soil color fill to L43. Clearned L43 and changed entire L34 and L43 to L44 as fill south of L42 surface. Still basically the same fill but different level.
very compacted clayey fill with areas of color changes that could indicated mudbrick collapse or wall.

arch:note.arch:string: Contexts excavated in trenches were recorded using the "locus system." A locus is any discrete three-dimensional entity excavated in a trench. The key to the locus system is the recognition that a locus is any one thing. Differences in soil composition or texture are therefore as important as, for example, the difference between a pit and a wall. If two entities were distinct, they were considered separate loci and were therefore assigned separate locus numbers. It should also be noted that every context excavated in a trench was given a locus number and thus the trench itself is made up completely of excavated loci.
